===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|Oracle bone script}}, a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} or {{liushu|ic|nocap=y}} – a person ({{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|人}}) lying on a bed ({{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|爿}}), sometimes with restless hands (compare the oracle-bone character for {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|丮}}) and sometimes with the eye ({{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|目}}) emphasized.

In the {{w|Bronze inscriptions}}, the eye ({{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|目}}) has eyebrows above it (compare {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|眉}}), and the person's body is attached underneath, now written as two dots on either side. The bed is no longer present, and instead {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|夕|t=moon; night}} has been added.

In the modern form 夢, the eyebrows are written {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|卝}}, the eyes are written {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|罒}}, and the person's body has become {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|冖}}, while {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|夕}} remains on the bottom.

According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', it is a {{Han compound|瞢|夕|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(s/r)-ma(ŋ/k)||dream}}; compare {{cog|bo|'''རྨང'''་ལམ|t=dream}}, {{cog|cdm|माङः||dream}}, {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*s-makᴴ ~ s-maŋ¹|*s-makᴴ ~ *s-maŋ¹|dream}}, {{cog|lus|mang||dream}}, {{cog|sit-jap|tɯ-jmŋo||dream}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques and Lai, 2019}}).

